    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.1"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>July 2, 1971</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I've just had a letter from the Swallow Press that sounds as if big things are happening to Black Elk and to the Memoir. Sounds great! Myrtle wrote that <hi rend="underline">Black Elk</hi> needed wider distribution; people wouldn't get it.</p> 
                
                <p>This is just a note to give our congratulations and say we still love you. We're enjoying London, and wish you were here; you'd like the green fields around and all the parks. All your books are in the British Museum, which shows they are right thinking. They've even got House's book!</p>
                
                <p>With it. I have more of your perspective on earlier years &#8212; you're doing so many things it's hard to sort out the most vital. Anyway, what matters most to <hi rend="underline">you</hi> is important.</p> 
                
                <p>I like your life, John. It says something aside from your work; actually it says the same thing your work says, but in a different way. The Chicago period says a mouthful!</p> 
                
                <p>I'll write you as soon as I get back from the ocean.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Love,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Lucile</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
                
                <note>N 40937 II           Printed in Western Germany</note> 
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>Standing on grass, and in front of a flowering plant, a little girl holding a basket of flowers</figDesc>
                    <p><unclear>Lore</unclear> L.</p>
                </figure>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.2"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">2</fw>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>I'll write you as soon as I have any. Take care of yourself and give my love to everyone. I'm sending this to Hilda's &#8212; I dont' have a firm address for you now. You'll hear from me soon again.</p> 
                    <closer>
                        <salute>Love,</salute>
                    
                        <signed>Lucile</signed> 
                    </closer>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
